d the government declared a three-day holiday. A French-speaker, who said he studied political science at <ORGANIZATION> Tehran </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> before he joined the communications services, said `` The Americans will come back now, I am sure. I do n't think it will take more than a few months.'' But on the 15-foot barbed-wire topped walls surrounding the vast grounds of the former <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> <ORGANIZATION> Embassy </ORGANIZATION>, bold English and <LOCATION> Farsi </LOCATION> writing painted years ago still boasted: `` We will make <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> face a severe defeat.''
