<FIRST>u f BC-BritishStocks     08-09 0198</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-British Stocks,0207</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Lower At Midday In Quiet Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Share prices were a bit lower across the board around midday Tuesday, with speculative activity providing the only excitement to an otherwise dull market. `` There is just very little business around in the market,'' one dealer said. `` Everybody's got flat books and no one cares which way the market goes.'' The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was down 2.9 points, or 0.2 percent, at 1,873.1 at about 12:30 p.m., just 0.3 point below its best level for the day. The index fluctuated in negative territory all morning, moving down as much as 7.3 points at one point. Volume was a light 222.1 million shares at midday, compared with 189.3 million shares at the same time Monday. A half-point increase in the British commercial banks' base lending rate to 11 percent on Monday, which had n't been expected and was the seventh rise since early June, apparently made investors reluctant to continue buying shares. At the same time, there was little selling pressure, dealers said. With activity in most stocks sharply reduced, attention turned to speculative situations, giving a boost to selected shares, they said.
</TEXT>
