<HEAD>Wal-Mart Earnings Soar 34 Percent; Limited Earnings Skid 46
Percent</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Wal-Mart </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stores </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>'s said Tuesday its profits soared 34 percent in the second quarter, while <ORGANIZATION> Limited </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which remained mired in the year-old apparel industry slump, said its earnings dropped 46 percent. <ORGANIZATION> Wal-Mart </ORGANIZATION> has been one of the few standouts in the struggling retail industry. The discount store chain said it earned $ 179.6 million, or 32 cents a share, in the quarter ended July 31, up from $ 134.1 million, or 24 cents a share, a year earlier. The company's sales increased in the latest quarter to $ 4.85 billion from $ 3.73 billion. Retail sales have fallen off over the past year in part because of women's disenchantment with fashions, but also because consumers have been trying to pay down their installment debt levels. Industry analysts say <ORGANIZATION> Wal-Mart </ORGANIZATION> consistently outperforms other retailers because of its competitive pricing. The company also has an efficient cost structure, enabling it to turn a large profit. Limited said its second-quarter earnings totaled $ 30.7 million, or 17 cents a share, down from $ 57.2 million, or 30 cents a share, in the same 1987 period. The apparel retailer's sales reached $ 893.1 million during the quarter, up from $ 822.1 million. Limited Chairman <PERSON> Leslie </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Wexner </PERSON> said the company anticipated relatively poor results and had kept its inventories at 1987 levels and controlled the markdowns that have eroded apparel retailers' earnings for a year Industry analysts believe the retailers will see signs of a recovery in the third quarter. Limited operates 3,252 specialty apparel stores under the names Limited, Express, <PERSON> Henri </PERSON> <PERSON> Bendel </PERSON>, <PERSON> Victoria </PERSON>'s Secret, <PERSON> Lerner </PERSON>, <PERSON> Lane </PERSON> <PERSO