mpared with $ 17.8 million for the same period last year. For the six months, net income was $ 1.4 billion, or $ 34.48 per share, comapred with $ 21.7 million, or 33 cents a share, in the same period last year. Revenue for the six months rose to $ 1 billion from $ 888 million in 1987.
